Summary of Terms (Plain English)
While the legal text above is the governing document, here is a simplified breakdown of what this means for DeskSave:

Commercial & Personal Use: You are free to use DeskSave for any purpose, including at work.

Copyleft: If you modify DeskSave and distribute it to others, you must keep the source code open and use this same GPL v3 license. You cannot make it "closed source."

Attribution: You must keep the original copyright notice and credit to Joshua Winkles intact.

No Warranty: The software is provided "as-is." The author is not liable for any issues arising from its use.

A Note on Selling: Under the GPL, you can actually charge a fee for the act of transferring a copy or providing support. However, because the license requires the source code to remain free and open, anyone you sell it to has the right to give it away for free themselves.

